content: I think the part that's become the most apparent the way I do things isn't how much I look for like Shortcuts. But I was watching a TSODING video where he talks about how you find the most direct path by doing the most indirect path. And it's starting to make more sense that way now where if you just do the work you know do the hard stuff push through to the end even if it means doing the most redundant things over and over again then inevitably you find something new.

Intentions
630 wake
640 meditate
730-1430 work (figure out deeper insecurities during 30 OR dream better version of self)
1500 1530 walk mu 
1530 1630 plan next year 
- Drum focus soloing or Afro Cuban?
- Financial focus, specifics of goals
- Intentions to change social situations 
1630 workout
What if the blog is just a daily dialogue on what I've learned?
Insecurity is rampant right now. That and anxiety is exacerbated by hunger.
Solution to writing problem is to write it out in a way others can play it and read it, not record it all myself
Create a consistent experience, so that if someone moves across the country, they'll get the same community. The same quality practice.

It's hard for me to imagine a business which doesn't promise the outcome of high achievement because I can't imagine a lifestyle that isn't built around that as a goal

It's hard for me to write the calm music I want to hear because I'm not a calm person

The thing I want to remember is that, even if this doesn't work, I'm building real skills and real relationships. If it doesn't work for drums, it still gives me the experience of building a business, of marketing, of being a leader of change. These are skillls that will take me anywhere. I started late, and am essentially starting my 20's over again but with more wisdom.

Rent a house as a home studio for lessons? Might be a better start than a retail space. Curious if this would be more appealing to the market than at a retail space 

Don't trust the direction that night time Zach wants to go in. Listen, but don't trust. Giving up is a projection of the exhaustion.
With this completionist energy, it feels so easy to songwrite. Just a matter of like get it down as quick as possible. Then when it comes time for the album, pick from the catalogue
